pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Waterproof gloves; Safety glasses or goggles; Shoes plus socks; NIOSH-approved particulate respirator with any N, R, or P filter with NIOSH approval prefix TC-84A; or NIOSH-approved powered air purifying respirator with an HE filter with NIOSH approval number prefix TC-21C

Active_Ingredients.name: Bacillus subtilis strain IAB/BS03
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Produces a broad-spectrum group of lipopeptides that disrupt pathogen cell-wall formation; colonizes the rhizosphere and leaves to prevent pathogen growth; stimulates phytohormones triggering induced systemic resistance

Safety_Information.general_Info: Harmful if swallowed or absorbed through skin. Causes moderate eye irritation. Avoid contact with eyes, skin or clothing. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco or using the toilet. Remove and wash contaminated clothing before reuse.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15 – 20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing eye. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not induce vomiting unless told to do so by the poison control center or doctor. Do not give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing. Rinse skin immediately with plenty of water for 15 – 20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
